name: cred-rea-fish-team-belt-transect-surveys-at-howland-island-2004
notes: Belt transects along 3 consecutively-placed, 25m transect lines were surveyed as part of Rapid Ecological Assessments conducted at 5 sites at Howland Island in January, 2004 NOAA vessel Oscar Elton Sette (OES04-01). Raw survey data included species level abundance estimates.
